JAVASCRIPT NOTES

1. JS console
-allows modification in real-time
-allows to run scripts (in console by inspecting the web page)
-debugging and fixing errors
-modify DOM

2. DOM Manipulation
-change HTML
      document.(html element to be changed).innerHTML="NEW HTML CODE "
-change CSS
      document.(select html element).style="css code"
-perform actions
      use js functions to perform actions on html elements

Chrome extensions can be developed with JS

3. JS with HTML & CSS

Query Selector:
-getELementById
-getElementByClassName

Above two selectors was used initially, but alternatively querySelector() method used.
document.querySelector("select elements as selected in CSS")

1. document.querySelector("elementName") i.e.  document.querySelector("h1")
2. document.querySelector("class name") i.e.  document.querySelector(".box")
3. document.querySelector("id of element") i.e.  document.querySelector("#box1")

4. Script Tag

added in the end of body so that javascript is loaded after HTML and CSS is loaded, 
if js loaded before html and css that page loading will take time


